sentence: But C.J.B. Marshall , vicar of a nearby church , feels the fault is in the stairs from the bell tower that are located next to the altar .
mut.sentence: But C.J.B. Marshall, vicar of a nearby church, feels the merit is in the stairs from the bell tower that are located next to the altar.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'stairs'的含义没有改变。原句中使用的'fault'和变异句中使用的'merit'是两个不同的形容词，分别表示楼梯的缺陷和优点，但这并不影响'stairs'这个词本身的含义，它在这两个句子中仍然指的是从钟楼通向圣坛的楼梯。

sentence: This building shook like hell and it kept getting stronger .
mut.sentence: This building shook like hell and it kept getting weaker.
reason: 原句中的目标词 'building' 所描述的状态是不断加强的震动，而变异句中的目标词 'building' 描述的状态是震动在减弱。因此，两个句子中目标词的具体含义存在明显差异。

sentence: The notion that tracking is somehow `` undemocratic `` is absurd .
mut.sentence: The notion that tracking is somehow `` democratic `` is absurd .
reason: 原句中的目标词'notion'指的是'追踪是某种程度上的“非民主”'的观念，而变异句中的目标词'notion'指的是'追踪是某种程度上的“民主”'的观念。两个句子中目标词'notion'的具体含义相反，因此结果为True。

sentence: One of the most provocative is that the intense reporting on the trial - including mainstream reporters ' extensive use of Twitter - created a `` circus atmosphere '' and such widespread , instant saturation with inflammatory details that the jury was improperly swayed by public passions .
mut.sentence: One of the most provocative is that the mild reporting on the trial - including mainstream reporters' extensive use of Twitter - created a `` circus atmosphere '' and such widespread, instant saturation with calming details that the jury was improperly swayed by public passions.
reason: 原句中的'reporting'使用了'intense'这个词来修饰，表示报道程度激烈、深入，而变异句中使用了'mild'来修饰'reporting'，表示报道程度温和、轻微。因此，两个句子中的目标词'reporting'含义有所不同。

sentence: The rest of the amount was taken from its own kitty , which was well filled through the sale of business units .
mut.sentence: The rest of the amount was left in its own kitty, which was well filled through the sale of business units.
reason: 原句中的目标词 'kitty' 指的是资金储备或资金来源，表示从这笔钱中取出了剩余的金额。而变异句中的 'kitty' 指的是这笔钱本身，表示剩余的金额仍然留存在资金储备中，没有动用。因此，两个句子中目标词的具体含义有所不同。

sentence: It flopped all around , real dramatic !
mut.sentence: It flopped all around, fake dramatic!
reason: 在原句中，'dramatic'用来形容'It flopped all around'的方式，意味着动作发生得非常戏剧化、引人注目。而在变异句中，'fake dramatic'表明这种戏剧化的表现是不真实的，是假装的。因此，两个句子中的目标词虽然都是'dramatic'，但前者的含义强调的是戏剧化的程度，后者则强调戏剧化的真实性。

sentence: No student should be permitted to be graduated from elementary school without having mastered the 3 R 's at the level that prevailed 20 years ago .
mut.sentence: No student should be permitted to be graduated from secondary school without having mastered the 3 R 's at the level that prevailed 20 years ago.
reason: 原句中的'level'指的是小学毕业生掌握3R（读、写、算）的水平，而变异句中的'level'指的是中学毕业生应达到的3R水平。由于小学和中学的教育阶段不同，因此这两个'level'所代表的学术水平要求是不同的。

sentence: Ray White in Utah and Walter Bodmer , a researcher in Great Britain , are close to finding another gene involved with some types of colon cancer , thought to be on chromosome 5 .
mut.sentence: Ray White in Utah and Walter Bodmer, a researcher in Great Britain, are close to finding another gene unrelated to some types of colon cancer, thought to be on chromosome 5.
reason: 原句中的'finding'指的是研究者们接近于找到与某些类型的结肠癌相关的基因，而变异句中的'finding'指的是研究者们接近于找到与某些类型的结肠癌无关的基因。两个句子中目标词'finding'的含义相反，因此结果为True。

sentence: US banks repay state support
mut.sentence: US banks owe state support
reason: 原句中的'support'指的是已经提供的帮助或资金支持，并且银行正在偿还这一支持。而变异句中的'support'意味着银行仍然欠着国家的支持，即还未偿还或未完成对国家的义务。因此，两个句子中'support'的含义和语境有所不同。

sentence: Technology securities have thereby lost some ground .
mut.sentence: Technology securities have thereby gained some ground.
reason: 在原句中，'lost some ground' 意味着技术证券失去了一部分优势或市场份额；而在变异句中，'gained some ground' 意味着技术证券获得了一些优势或市场份额。因此，两个句子中的目标词 'ground' 在含义上相反，表示动作的不同方向，一个是失去，另一个是获得。

sentence: You see , I always make it look like an accident .
mut.sentence: You see, I never make it look like an accident.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'look' 的含义并没有改变。'look' 在这里都是用作动词，表示让某物看起来像是某种情况或状态。原句中的 'always' 和变异句中的 'never' 改变的是动作发生的频率，而不是 'look' 的含义。

sentence: You did not note that the homeless people we examined had a multitude of physical disorders in addition to their psychiatric problems and substance abuse .
mut.sentence: You did not note that the housed people we examined had a multitude of physical disorders in addition to their psychiatric problems and substance abuse.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词 'had' 在句子中的含义相同，都表示过去发生的动作或存在的状态，即指被检查的人拥有（存在）多种身体疾病、精神问题以及药物滥用。这里的 'had' 是动词 'have' 的过去式，用于描述过去的事实或情况，并不因为句子中的其他词汇变化（如 'homeless' 变为 'housed'）而改变其本身的含义。

sentence: Nobody witnessed the fall -- just the sickening impact when his body smashed on the pavement just outside the basement delivery entrance .
mut.sentence: Nobody witnessed the rise -- just the sickening impact when his body smashed on the pavement just outside the basement delivery entrance.
reason: 原句中的目标词 'witnessed' 指的是目击或见证了一个事件的发生，在这里是指没有人看到他摔倒的过程；而变异句中的目标词 'witnessed' 指的是目击或见证了一个上升的动作，这与原句中的含义完全不同，因为上升和下降是两个相反的动作。

sentence: Back in the chase car , we drove around some more , got stuck in a ditch , enlisted the aid of a local farmer to get out the trailer hitch and pull us out of the ditch .
mut.sentence: Back in the chase car, we drove straight some more, got stuck in a ditch, enlisted the aid of a local farmer to get out the trailer hitch and pull us out of the ditch.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词'pull'含义相同，都指的是用力将车从沟渠中拉出来。'pull'在这里表示的是一种物理动作，没有因为句子中的其他词汇变化而改变其基本含义。原句中的'some more'和变异句中的'straight some more'是描述驾驶方式的差异，并不影响'pull'这个词的含义。

sentence: If these assumptions hold , voters in races for Congress face what in economic theory is called a prisoner 's dilemma and have an incentive , at the margin , to lean Democratic .
mut.sentence: If these assumptions hold, voters in races for Congress face what in economic theory is called a prisoner's dilemma and have an incentive, at the margin, to lean Republican.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'lean'的含义相同，都指的是在政治倾向上偏向某个党派。原句中是'Democratic'（民主党），变异句中是'Republican'（共和党），但'lean'本身表示的倾向、倾斜、偏向的意思没有改变。

sentence: I know many schoolteachers and , on the whole , they are seriously committed to conscientious teaching .
mut.sentence: I know many schoolteachers and, on the whole, they are seriously uncommitted to conscientious teaching.
reason: 原句中的'seriously'用来加强肯定语气，表示老师们非常致力于认真教学；而变异句中的'seriously'用来加强否定语气，表示老师们在认真教学方面非常不投入。因此，两个句子中的'seriously'在含义上存在明显差异。

sentence: Dr. Knudson found that some children with the eye cancer had inherited a damaged copy of chromosome No. 13 from a parent who had had the disease .
mut.sentence: Dr. Knudson found that some children with the eye cancer had inherited a healthy copy of chromosome No. 13 from a parent who had had the disease.
reason: 原句中的目标词'No.'在此上下文中指的是特定的染色体编号，即第13号染色体，且该染色体是受损的。而变异句中的目标词'No.'虽然指的也是第13号染色体，但此处描述的是该染色体是健康的。因此，两个句子中目标词的具体含义有所不同，一个是受损的染色体，另一个是健康的染色体。

sentence: There is evidence that if people inherit defective versions of these genes , they are especially prone to cancer , perhaps explaining , finally , why some cancers seem to haunt certain families .
mut.sentence: There is evidence that if people inherit functional versions of these genes, they are especially prone to cancer, perhaps explaining, finally, why some cancers seem to haunt certain families.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'inherit' 的含义没有改变。无论是 'defective versions of these genes' 还是 'functional versions of these genes'，'inherit' 都表示从父母那里遗传基因的过程。变异句中的 'functional' 与原句中的 'defective' 是形容词，用来描述遗传的基因版本的状态，而并不影响 'inherit' 这个动词本身的含义。

sentence: I know many schoolteachers and , on the whole , they are seriously committed to conscientious teaching .
mut.sentence: I know many schoolteachers and, on the whole, they are seriously uncommitted to conscientious teaching.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'teaching'的含义并没有改变。原句中的'teaching'指的是老师们认真负责的教学行为，而变异句中的'teaching'依然是描述老师们的教学行为，只是加上了'uncommitted'这个形容词表明老师们没有投入到这种认真负责的教学中。因此，尽管态度不同，但'teaching'本身的含义没有区别。

sentence: The United States is not going to do a deal without the major developing countries stepping up and taking action , said Stern , who also complained that the text did not do enough to make sure the cuts could be verified by outside observers .
mut.sentence: The United States is going to do a deal with the major developing countries stepping down and avoiding action, said Stern, who also complained that the text did too much to make sure the cuts could not be verified by outside observers.
reason: 原句中的'do a deal'指的是美国与其他主要发展中国家达成一项协议，强调需要这些国家参与并采取行动。而变异句中的'do a deal'则是指美国可能与这些国家达成一项协议，但这些国家却在回避行动，且变异句中提到协议内容过多地确保了削减措施无法被外部观察者验证，与原句的含义和目的相反。
